    "name": "Above & Beyond",
    "profile": "English electronic music group. Above & Beyond came together in 2000 originally to complete a remix of [a=Chakra]'s \"[m=110296]\" for [l=WEA].\r\nInitially producing strictly trance music, the trio gradually moved forwards progressive trance and house sounds, occasionally releasing downtempo and ambient tracks.\r\n\r\n[a=Jono Grant] and [a=Paavo Siljamäki] had met at Westminster University and launched [l=Anjunabeats] label in summer 1999 with a track titled \"[m=26011]\", released with an equal artist name to the label [a=Anjunabeats] in 2000. For the duo's second track release in 2000 titled \"[m=19050]\" as [a=Free State] and their third in 2001 titled \"[m=19056]\".\r\n\r\nAlerted to the pair by his brother [a=Liam McGuinness], producer [a=Tony McGuinness] called in Jono and Paavo to help him complete the Chakra remix while he was still working at WEA. With Grant and Siljamäki teaming up with McGuiness to form a trio, Above & Beyond became their artists name. They plucked the name Above & Beyond fr",
